Description: Fragment of a wooden coffin; paint on plaster; row of Hieroglyphic text in blue.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Curator's comments: Part of the same coffin as EA46641-556-8 and EA47594-602 according to Zitman 2010, 115, 230 (II). The top edge of the board is painted red.
Bibliographic references: Zitman 2010 / The necropolis of Assiut: a case study of local Egyptian funerary culture from the Old Kingdom to the end of the Middle Kingdom (II, 115, 230)
